Carbide / Graphite plans $ 28 mln upgrade . Carbide / Graphite Group Inc said on Monday it plans to build a $ 28 million longitudinal graphitizing facility to replace less efficient Acheson graphitizing facilities . The project , which is subject to regulatory and environmental approvals , will be funded from internal cash flow and credit facilities , the company said in a statement . Walter Flower , the company ' s chief executive , said the new facility would provide " a manufacturing cost advantage of almost 20 cents a pound , a shorter inventory cycle of eight days versus 24 days , as well as significant processing advantages . " Carbide / Graphite is currently involved in two other modernization projects in its graphite electrode facilities , the company said . Carbide / Graphite manufactures industial graphite and calcium carbide products . 
